Brazil Stock Movers: Gol Linhas Aereas, Tam Gain; Vale Falls

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-08-19T20:23:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/brazil-stock-movers-gol-linhas-mpx-advance-vale-falls.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 1.3 percent to 52,447.63.  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA (GOLL4)  (GOLL4 BS) gained 1.1
percent to 10.22 reais while  Tam SA (TAMM4)  (TAMM4 BS) rose 1.9 percent
to 29.70 reais.  Brazil ’s demand for domestic flights grew 20
percent in July from a year earlier, while the occupancy rate
rose to 75 percent, said the country’s civil aviation regulator,
known as Anac. For international flights, demand increased 10
percent and the occupancy rate reached 85 percent, Anac said in
an e-mailed statement.  Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS) slid 2.6 percent to 37.31 reais. The
miner is considering selling its stake in shipping-container
unit Log-In Logistica Intermodal SA and creating a rail-
transport arm for general cargo,  Valor Economico  reported,
without saying where it got the information. Vale declined to
comment on the possible sale of Log-In because it doesn’t
respond to market rumors, according to Valor.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
